The paper discusses the problem of learning efficient representations for intelligent agents, which is a central topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on disentangled representation learning, which is a popular approach for separating out the underlying structure of the world into disjoint parts of its representation. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
